                    <p>Artist: Boris Kollar </p>
                    <p>Title: <em> Unspecified</em></p>
                    <p>Do you consider a plant or a child to be a design of a man? 
                        “It is not an object”, they would say, “It has a life of its own”. 
                        But then, you are the one who take care of it, 
                        who gives it water and who turns it towards the sun for it to grow. 
                        I design.
                        I cut a fabric then I stitch it, 
                        I create a garment, which I eventually sell for it to leave my house and live its own life too. 
                        “But it is an object”, they would say. 
                        But then, is there a  difference between an object and a plant or a child?
                    </p>
